articles.author: David Close and Matias Grez, CNN
articles.title: Nine of 12 Super League clubs recommit to UEFA and admit project was a mistake - CNN International
articles.description: European football's governing body, UEFA, says nine of the 12 founding clubs that formed the ill-fated breakaway Super League competition have recommitted to UEFA club and national team competitions.

articles.author: Sky
articles.title: European Super League: Nine rebel clubs accept sanctions and commit their future to UEFA competitions - Sky News
articles.description: And as a "gesture of goodwill" the clubs will also donate £13m, to children's, youth and grassroots football clubs across Europe.

articles.title: How a student's hunt for free software led to a research institute being crippled by ransomware - IT World Canada
articles.description: A student's eagerness for free software and the willingness of the European biomolecular research institute he worked at to allow personal computers for network access recently proved to be a terrible combination.
